title: Power repeats itself.

author: Russell Brand
description:
Why are 7,000 football fans chanting the same expletive at the British Prime Minister? Why is a woman in jail for a single post? Why is a Republican quoting graphic sex scenes from schoolbooks in public chambers? This isn’t just about Keir Starmer or cultural decline—it’s about a deeper, spiritual erosion of meaning, identity, and free speech in the UK. In today’s episode, we dive into the contradictions, hypocrisies, and outright madness defining modern Britain, from censorship and stadium protests to collapsing political trust and the sacred turned profane. You’ll laugh, you’ll weep, you’ll pray. Maybe all at once.
